comment_data.body:
I'm entirely uncertain of how this issue could happen:

```
java.lang.IncompatibleClassChangeError: Method com.intellij.openapi.roots.impl.libraries.ProjectLibraryTable.getInstance(Lcom/intellij/openapi/project/Project;)Lcom/intellij/openapi/roots/libraries/LibraryTable; must be InterfaceMethodref 
	at io.flutter.sdk.FlutterSdkManager.<init>(FlutterSdkManager.java:41)
```

It looks like IntelliJ is trying to hot reload changes into the JVM?

I assume a restart took care of the issue. I'm going to close this, as the resolution isn't clear, but if we get other similar reports, we'll investigate. Thanks for the report!
